\par\par \uc2 Ethereum\par \b \uc2 Ethereum Breaks Past $2,000 for the First Time as DeFi's Total Revenue Hits $800 Million\b0\par\par\uc2 Brian Njuguna \par \uc2 354 \uc2 words\par \uc2 22 February 2021\par \uc2 Blockchain.News\par \uc2 BLCRNW\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2021. Worldmoney Blockchain Management Co., Limited \par \par \uc2 Ethereum (ETH) is on fire as it continues making moves not seen in its 6-year history. Ether has broken the record by surging past the $2,000 mark across major exchanges.\par \par \uc2 The second cryptocurrency based on market capitalization is up by 8.94% in the last seven days and is {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://twitter.com/iamjosephyoung/status/1362964870962974721"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 trading}}}\uc2  at $2,013.00 at the time of writing, according to CoinMarketCap.\par \par \uc2 Crypto whales have been showing interest in Ethereum because addresses holding more than $10,000 ETH {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://blockchain.news/news/ethereum-crosses-1-900-first-time-history-total-value-locked-eth-2-hits-all-time-high"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 ballooned}}}\uc2  to1,287 on Valentine's Day, which has been pivotal in boosting Ethereum's uptrend.\par \par \uc2 Yann Jan, the co-founders of leading on-chain data provider Glassnode, has {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://twitter.com/Negentropic_/status/1362832932247900166"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 disclosed}}}\uc2  that there are currently at least 100,000 BTC and ETH addresses that hold more than $1 million.\par \par \uc2 Total Revenue in DeFi Hits $800 Million in January\par \par \uc2 Ethereum's present bull run is being boosted by ETH 2.0 {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://blockchain.news/news/ethereum-2-goes-live-eth-plunges-here-what-need-know"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 going live}}}\uc2  in December 2021 amid a booming decentralized finance (DeFi) sector. ETH 2.0 offers a transition to the proof-of-stake consensus mechanism from the current proof-of-work as proof-of-stake protocols are deemed more \uc2 environmental\uc2  and cost-friendly.\par \par \uc2 DeFi is proving to be a force to be reckoned within the crypto space as it {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://blockchain.news/news/defi-projects-continue-generate-huge-returns-decoupling-bitcoin-is-observed"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 exploded}}}\uc2  and grew exponentially in 2020, with Ethereum benefitting from its rise in popularity.\par \par \uc2 Crypto trader Alex Kruger has taken to \uc2 Twitter\uc2  to disclose that the total fees paid in DeFi have soared to $800 million this month. He {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://twitter.com/krugermacro/status/1362957129989058564"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 noted}}}\uc2 :\par \par \uc2 Next time you hear someone say there is no real demand for crypto assets and how crypto is not productive, show him this.\par \par \uc2 Michael van de Poppe, a crypto analyst, trusts that Ethereum is continuously showing bullish signals.\par \par \uc2 ETH has begun 2021 with a bang, and it seems that the sky is the limit because more institutional investors are keeping a keen eye on Ether, as {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://twitter.com/Grayscale/status/1362879032245833729"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 evidenced}}}\uc2  by Grayscale's Ethereum Trust portfolio of $6.1 billion, a figure that continues to grow by the day.\par \par \uc2 Document BLCRNW0020210222eh2m0000a\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw200\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal3000\pichgoal600
