n transaction consumed the same amount of electricity as the average US household would in a twenty-day span.\par \par \uc2 Proof-of-stake (PoS) blockchains might therefore be a more viable alternative to Proof-of-Work (PoW) protocols, according to industry experts. As Pos blockchains utilize cryptography, the required processing power needed is significantly lower than PoW transactions.\par \par \uc2 Currently, Ethereum aims to make the transition from a proof-of-work consensus to a pure proof-of-stake mainnet. Once Ethereum 2.0 is completed, the upgrade will {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://blockchain.news/news/ethereum-gains-10m-investment-20-eth-2.0-target-staked-vitalik-buterin-discusses-expectations"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 enable}}}\uc2  transactions in a more energy efficient way, in addition to other benefits such as better scalability.\par \par \uc2 Document BLCRNW0020210210eh2a00001\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw200\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal3000\pichgoal600
