\par\par \uc2 Press Release\par \b \uc2 Business of Design Week 2020 Summit Concludes First Hybrid Live Edition Captures Trends Redefined by World\u8217\'20\'19s Top Creative Minds for the Post-pandemic Era\b0\par\par\uc2 Ellie Suen \par \uc2 1,078 \uc2 words\par \uc2 16 December 2020\par \uc2 Blockchain.News\par \uc2 BLCRNW\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2020. Worldmoney Blockchain Management Co., Limited \par \par \uc2 Business of Design Week 2020 Summit Concludes First Hybrid Live Edition Captures Trends Redefined by World's Top Creative Minds for the Post-pandemic Era\par \par \uc2 Over 50 Sessions Available On-Demand Online from 18 December onwards\par \par \uc2 Business of Design Week (BODW) , Asia's annual flagship event on design, innovation and brands held its 2020 edition from 30 November to 5 December. Organised by Hong Kong Design Centre (HKDC) and co-organised by \uc2 Hong Kong Trade Development Council (HKTDC)\uc2 , with Create Hong Kong (CreateHK) of the Government of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR Government) as the Lead Sponsor, BODW 2020 was successfully concluded with its BODW Summit held as a hybrid event simulcast live on multiple platforms for the first time. From 3 to 5 December, the BODW 2020 Summit connected global creative visionaries with international participants from around the world in over 50 sessions.\par \par \uc2 Under the theme VISION 20/21', the BODW Summit addressed timely themes relevant to the post-pandemic era to help participants find clarity in uncertainty. Over 100 influential design and business leaders shared their views on nine themes, namely Brand Futures, Connected Health, Safe Travels, Circular Economy, Immersive Tech, Creative Leadership, Entwined Spaces, Communication Design and Culture the City. With the support of the UK as Strategic Partner, this year's programme featured a new BODW Great British Design video series, showcasing the designs of 14 creative leaders from the UK. Past talks from nine global celebrated creative pioneers were also featured in BODW Greatest Moments that were part of the Summit programme.\par \par \uc2 In partnership with the Summit's Production and TV Broadcaster, ViuTV, BODW produced a number of the sessions in hybrid live format for streaming on BODW's customised virtual platform. From 3 to 5 December, selective sessions were further simulcast on ViuTVsix every evening Hong Kong time, as well as on social media platforms, and to an in-person audience at the BODW CitySalon partner locations at D2 Place and Fashion Walk.\par \par \uc2 Sessions from the BODW Summit (including MasterClasses) will be available on demand from 18 December 2020 onwards, with more details to be announced at {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.bodw.com/pr"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 www.bodw.com/pr}}}\uc2 . In addition, a TV programme of BODW Summit highlights will be aired on ViuTV Channel 99 on 19 December 2020 at 19:30 20:00 GMT+8.\par \par \uc2 Prof. Eric Yim, Chairman of Hong Kong Design Centre , said, Through Business of Design Week, we are committed to promoting the power of innovative design in Hong Kong, and across the world. At this year's BODW Summit, over 100 influential design and business leaders gathered together and explored some of the critical topics that will redefine the pandemic era, and inspire us to imagine new possibilities for the future.\par \par \uc2 Here are some thought-provoking insights from this year's BODW speakers, grouped by themes explored during the Summit:\par \par \uc2 Creative Leadership What is Next For Design Now, Near and Far\par \par \uc2 Tim Brown (US), Chair of IDEO , said, Organisations with existing design capacity were able to respond more quickly (to the pandemic). This shows that investing in design makes society more resilient to unexpected shocks.\par \par \uc2 Brand Futures TOMorrow: Designer Brands after 2020\par \par \uc2 Tom Dixon OBE (UK), Designer Creative Director of Tom Dixon , said The combination of the digital, handmade and personal will be the interesting evolution in terms of design thinking.\par \par \uc2 Entwined Spaces Melting the Boundary: Live/Work\par \par \uc2 Keith Griffiths (Hong Kong), Chairman Global Design Principal of Aedas , said, So if everybody's buying products online, what is the purpose of shopping (at physical shops)? What's the purpose of a (physical) shop? We as human beings need to socialise. These palaces of purchasing called shopping malls will no longer be places where we just buy products. They'll be places where we go to meet to exchange news.\par \par \uc2 Safe Travels Designing Tomorrow's Travel Experience\par \par \uc2 Paul Priestman (UK), Designer, Co-founder Chairman of PriestmanGoode , said, The contactless journey is a key part of transport design thinking - how do we ease the customer journey in travel, removing the stopping points. Key to design of big airports and stations is to help make the journey secure, safe but also enjoyable.\par \par \uc2 Circular Economy Circular Magic in Nature, \uc2 People and Planet\par \par \uc2 Lay Koon Tan (UK), Co-founder of Nature Squared said, Today's \uc2 environmental\uc2  imperatives are global poverty and inequality. All these issues are very widely publicised. We felt strongly that if we want to make a difference, however small, we can contribute to sustainable development. We needed to come up with an answer that was holistic and would address \uc2 environmental\uc2 , social and financial responsibilities.\par \par \uc2 Immersive Tech Design x Art x Tech: Stroke of Human Touch\par \par \uc2 Victor Wong (Hong Kong), Founder of vfxNova said, For me, the work of AI is not just to mimic the work of humans. I think we should find a way to cooperate with AI to do something that humans cannot do. So the process inspires us to do the next.\par \par \uc2 About Hong Kong Design Centre\par \par \uc2 Hong Kong Design Centre (HKDC) is a non-governmental organisation, and was founded in 2001 as a strategic partner of the HKSAR Government in establishing Hong Kong as an international centre of design excellence in Asia. Our public mission is to promote wider and strategic use of design and design thinking to create business value and improve societal well- being, with the aim of advancing Hong Kong as an international design centre in Asia. Learn more about us at {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.hkdesigncentre.org"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 www.hkdesigncentre.org }}}\par \par \uc2 About Create Hong Kong\par \par \uc2 Create Hong Kong (CreateHK) is a dedicated agency set up by the HKSAR Government in June 2009. It is under the Communications and Creative Industries Branch of the Commerce and Economic Development Bureau and dedicated to spearheading the development of creative industries in Hong Kong. Its strategic foci are nurturing talent and facilitating start-ups, exploring markets, and promoting Hong Kong as Asia's creative capital and fostering a creative atmosphere in the community. CreateHK sponsors HKDC to organise BODW and other\par \par \uc2 projects to promote Hong Kong design. CreateHK's website: {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.createhk.gov.hk"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 www.createhk.gov.hk}}}\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 Media Contact\par \par \uc2 For further enquiries or interview requests, please contact: Tiffany Ho | {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "mailto:tiffany.ho@fleishman.com"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 tiffany.ho@fleishman.com}}}\uc2  | (852) 2586 7867 / 6089 9273\par \par \uc2 Charlie So | {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "mailto:charlie.so@fleishman.com"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 charlie.so@fleishman.com}}}\uc2  | (852) 2586 7850 / 9326 8267\par \par \uc2 Document BLCRNW0020201216egcg00009\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw200\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal3000\pichgoal600
