\par\par \uc2 Cryptoeconomics\par \b \uc2 Universal Carbon UPCO2: World\u8217\'20\'19s First Carbon Off-Set Token Now Tradable on Uphold Platform\b0\par\par\uc2 Lucas Cacioli \par \uc2 791 \uc2 words\par \uc2 2 December 2020\par \uc2 Blockchain.News\par \uc2 BLCRNW\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2020. Worldmoney Blockchain Management Co., Limited \par \par \uc2 Universal Carbon (UPCO2), the world's first tradable carbon token is now available on Uphold, a digital money platform serving more than 3 million customers in more than 150 countries.\par \par \uc2 UPCO2 is now available on Uphold, to trade or to offset corporate carbon footprints with each token representing one ton per year of carbon dioxide.\par \par \uc2 The Universal Protocol Alliance (UPA), a coalition of leading blockchain companies including Bittrex Global, Ledger, Certik, Infinigold and Uphold, today launches Universal Carbon (UPCO2), the world's first tradable carbon token on a public blockchain that can be bought and held as an investment or burnt to offset an individual's carbon footprint.\par \par \uc2 With demand for carbon credits outstripping supply by a factor of 4 to 1 in 2020, according to the \uc2 World Bank\uc2 , the UPCO2 Token is set to democratize an important new asset class, which could lead to the establishment of a global clearing price for carbon (as today exists for such commodities as oil and gold) and more resources going into \uc2 environmental\uc2  projects.\par \par \uc2 Each UPCO2 Token represents one year-ton of CO2 pollution averted by a certified REDD+ project preventing rainforest loss or degradation. Every Token is backed by a Voluntary Carbon Unit, VCU, a digital certificate issued by Verra, the international standards agency, which allows certified projects to turn their greenhouse gas (GHG) reductions into tradable carbon credits.\par \par \uc2 UP Alliance Chairman, Matthew Le Merle:\par \par \uc2 The projects we support through carbon credit purchases prevent deforestation in the Amazon, Congo Basin and Indonesia as well as other threatened rainforests[ ] For a new generation of investors looking for more than mere financial return, UPCO2 offers attractive social, economic and \uc2 environmental\uc2  benefits. At a key moment for \uc2 climate change\uc2 , UPCO2 allows people worldwide to do good for the planet and potentially do well for themselves.\par \par \uc2 Powerful macroeconomic forces underpin the Voluntary Carbon Credit market and, according to some commentators, could drive up prices significantly as more countries introduce regulated CO2 markets, forcing companies to compensate for their pollution. Additionally, a growing number of firms and individuals are choosing to offset their carbon footprints voluntarily.\par \par \uc2 Combating \uc2 Climate Change\uc2  with Tokenization\par \par \uc2 Universal Protocol Alliance's vision is that every asset class will be digitized and tokenized.\par \par \uc2 According to the \uc2 World Bank\uc2 , in 2020, humanity compensates for just 22% of global emissions through the purchase and retirement of carbon credits, and yet the proportion of countries operating regulated carbon markets has risen from 40 percent of global GDP in 2016 to 70 percent in 2020. The result is a wall of demand that may far outstrip the production of new carbon credits, which is choked by the slow and expensive process of Voluntary Carbon Project certification.\par \par \uc2 This year may go down as the key inflection point for \uc2 climate change\uc2 , said JP Thieriot, Co-Founder of the UP Alliance and CEO of Uphold. The year it went from a far-off issue enshrined in distant accords like Kyoto and Paris, to an existential threat affecting the lives of tens of millions of people. In recent months, we've seen Australia and California on fire, ever more powerful hurricanes, the US president-elect Joe Biden announcing a Climate Administration, and companies such as Apple, \uc2 Microsoft\uc2 , and \uc2 Nike\uc2  voluntarily committing to carbon neutrality.\par \par \uc2 Thieriot added:\par \par \uc2 Combating \uc2 climate change\uc2  is likely to become the dominant economic issue of the next 20 years. The UPCO2 Token allows people everywhere to participate in this hugely important - and potentially lucrative - new market, as well as do the right thing for the planet.\par \par \uc2 Voluntary carbon credits, which back all UPCO2 Tokens, offer major economic advantages compared with regulated credits. As dollar-denominated, globally-recognized, fungible and perennial assets, voluntary credits last forever, maintaining option value, until consumed or retired by a company or an individual seeking to compensate for carbon footprint.\par \par \uc2 It's astonishing that there is no single global clearing price for carbon emissions, said Le Merle. A non-deliverable, digitally-tradable commodity that's essential for human activity shouldn't be traded bilaterally on OTC markets, as carbon credits are today. One year-ton of carbon means the same everywhere. As a globally-recognized asset, defined by international standards, a Voluntary Carbon Credit should eventually fetch the same price anywhere.\par \par \uc2 Matthew Le Merle said:\par \par \uc2 We believe that the UPCO2 token has an important role to play in democratizing access to carbon credits, which could eliminate price arbitrage and produce a single global price. This was a light bulb going on for me. Combine a digital asset with a rainforest carbon offset and give everyone in the world access. How could that not be a great idea?\par \par \uc2 Document BLCRNW0020201202egc200004\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw200\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal3000\pichgoal600
