\par\par \uc2 Ethereum\par \b \uc2 More Than 50% of ETH Has Now Been Staked in Preparation for Ethereum 2.0 Mainnet\b0\par\par\uc2 Shine Li \par \uc2 485 \uc2 words\par \uc2 24 November 2020\par \uc2 Blockchain.News\par \uc2 BLCRNW\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2020. Worldmoney Blockchain Management Co., Limited \par \par \uc2 With just a week left before Ethereum 2.0's launch, the deposit contracts that are needed for the blockchain upgrade to happen have surged and topped 50% of its target.\par \par \uc2 A total of 524,888 Ether (ETH) are needed for ETH 2.0 mainnet to launch on December 1. This equates to 32 ETH per validator. At the time of writing, Ethereum's launch pad has {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://launchpad.ethereum.org/"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 recorded}}}\uc2  that 294,304 ETH has been locked in, an impressive amount staked considering the lack of validators that was {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://blockchain.news/news/ethereum-gains-10m-investment-20-eth-2.0-target-staked-vitalik-buterin-discusses-expectations"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 reported}}}\uc2  last week.\par \par \uc2 According to lead Ethereum coordinator Danny Ryan, the staked investments must be locked in seven days before December 1. If the required amount of Ether is not locked in by November 24, the genesis of ETH 2.0 will once again be delayed.\par \par \uc2 Co-founder Vitalik Buterin has taken the optimistic approach as validator participation seems to have surged in a short period of time. Compared to last week, when the staking balance was just nearing 20% of its threshold, this is good progress. Buterin {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://twitter.com/VitalikButerin?ref_src=twsrc%5Egoogle%7Ctwcamp%5Eserp%7Ctwgr%5Eauthor"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 tweeted}}}\uc2 :\par \par \uc2 The #eth2 deposit contract has reached more than half of its target (currently at ~278000 ETH deposited), with the bulk of the deposits taking place in the last three days!\par \par \uc2 Why will the beacon chain be better than a PoW blockchain?\par \par \uc2 The Ethereum 2.0 mainnet will feature the first phase of the new blockchain update, which will be a beacon chain. The mainnet's goal will be to transition to a pure proof-of-stake protocol, as opposed to the proof-of-work (PoW) consensus many cryptocurrencies such as Bitcoin run on.\par \par \uc2 An Ethereum pioneer retweeted by Buterin vouched for Ethereum's beacon chain's efficacy and faster transaction time in comparison with a proof-of-work chain. In addressing what should be expected of the beacon chain, he said:\par \par \uc2 Faster sync times, better light client guarantees, reduced (maybe 0) selfish mining' risk, per-confirm reversion probability much lower in normal case (no attacks + good global network latency), better randomness, reduced losses if unexpected quantum breakthroughs appear.\par \par \uc2 According to many, the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://blockchain.news/news/ethereum-gains-10m-investment-20-eth-2.0-target-staked-vitalik-buterin-discusses-expectations"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 proof-of-stake model}}}\uc2  will also be great for \uc2 sustainability\uc2 , as it will be more energy-efficient than proof-of-work blockchains. In addition, stakers stand to gain more profits with ETH 2.0, and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://blockchain.news/news/ethereum-zinken-testnet-launch-is-huge-success-buterin-scalability-will-go-up-eth-2"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 scalability}}}\uc2  the computing power or the amount of transactions that can be processed by software at a given time will also be increased.\par \par \uc2 In tandem with Ethereum's anticipated mainnet launch and Bitcoin's bullish rally, Ethereum's price has also {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://blockchain.news/news/ethereum-price-rallies-eth-whales-smallest-percentage-supply-11-months"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 skyrocketed}}}\uc2 . It has gained over 24% in the past week, currently {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://coinmarketcap.com/"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 trading}}}\uc2  north of $580 on CoinMarketCap. On-chain analytics also found that new Ethereum addresses have been increasing, which may imply that there has been renewed interest in the altcoin.\par \par \uc2 Document BLCRNW0020201124egbo00009\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw200\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal3000\pichgoal600
