\par\par \uc2 Bitcoin\par \b \uc2 Ripple CEO Says Bitcoin PoW Energy Use Makes Square Target of Biden\u8217\'20\'19s \uc2 Climate Change\uc2  Agenda\b0\par\par\uc2 Lucas Cacioli \par \uc2 498 \uc2 words\par \uc2 11 November 2020\par \uc2 Blockchain.News\par \uc2 BLCRNW\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2020. Worldmoney Blockchain Management Co., Limited \par \par \uc2 Ripple CEO Brad Garlinghouse thinks Bitcoin's massive energy consumption through proof-of-work (PoW) could make public companies like Square, who invested heavily in BTC, potential targets of US election winner Joe Biden's \uc2 climate change\uc2  agenda. Garlinghouse used the opportunity to highlight XRP's superior energy efficiency.\par \par \uc2 President-elect Joe Biden is predicted to realign the United States with the global \uc2 climate change\uc2  agenda and could put requirements on public companies to disclose green house gas (GHG) emissions. Ripple's CEO Garlinghouse took to \uc2 twitter\uc2  to single out Square and said \uc2 Jack Dorsey\uc2 's payments company should pay attention after their $50 million dollar BTC investment.\par \par \uc2 On Monday Nov. 10, Ripple CEO Garlinghouse leant his comments to an earlier {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://twitter.com/nytpolitics/status/1325578375004643328"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 tweet}}}\uc2  from NYT politics that highlighted the incoming president's previously proposed measure on \uc2 climate change\uc2 . The tweet outlined Biden's promise to rejoin the Paris Agreement, which was {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.whitehouse.gov/briefings-statements/statement-president-trump-paris-climate-accord/"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 snubbed}}}\uc2  by the Trump administration in 2017.\par \par \uc2 The Ripple CEO tweeted that President-elect Biden will be much tougher on \uc2 climate change\uc2  than Trump and require all public companies to disclose their GHG production. Garlinghouse also singled out Jack Dorsey's Square, saying the payments firm should pay attention to the new guidelines expected from the Biden administration.\par \par \uc2 The Ripple CEO {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://twitter.com/bgarlinghouse/status/1325842115880914944"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 said}}}\uc2 :\par \par \uc2 Biden to require public companies to disclose \uc2 climate change\uc2 -related activities and GHG emissions in their operations. Love to see the action on \uc2 climate change\uc2  - first NYDFS, now this. Public companies holding BTC (ahem Square) -- may want to pay attention.\par \par \uc2 The power consumption of the Bitcoin proof-of-work (PoW) network has been a huge point of contention for the premier cryptocurrency. In a publication on the Ripple website entitled, The \uc2 Environmental\uc2  Impact: Cryptocurrency Mining vs. Consensus , Bitcoin's PoW power consumption is used to highlight the superiority of Ripple's XRP token.\par \par \uc2 Ripple compares power usage through light bulbs explaining that every 1 million XRP transactions uses enough power to a lightbulb for 79,000 hours, while 1 million BTC transactions on Bitcoin's PoW network would power the lightbulb for 4.51 billion hours.\par \par \uc2 Public Companies Pay Attention\par \par \uc2 The has been a slew of publicly traded companies that have {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://blockchain.news/news/public-companies-now-hold-almost-7-billion-worth-of-bitcoin"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 invested}}}\uc2  massively into Bitcoin as of late, which according to Garlinghouse may be an issue for them as given the potential incoming green compliance legislation.\par \par \uc2 Ripple CEO Garlinghouse pointed to Square in his tweet. Last month \uc2 Jack Dorsey\uc2 , CEO of Twitter and payments processing service Square, publicly tweeted that Square had invested $50 million of the company's holdings into Bitcoin purchasing 4,709 BTC.\par \par \uc2 If Square should take notice of the Biden administration's incoming plan for \uc2 climate change\uc2 , then \uc2 MicroStrategy\uc2  who has also purchased 38,250 Bitcoin as its reserve treasury asset just under $600 million at the time of writing should definitely sit up and take notice of the Democrat's green agenda.\par \par \uc2 Document BLCRNW0020201111egbb00004\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw200\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal3000\pichgoal600
