\par\par \uc2 Altcoins\par \b \uc2 Ripple CTO Explains Why Banks Have Been Lagging Behind on XRP Adoption\b0\par\par\uc2 Shine Li \par \uc2 396 \uc2 words\par \uc2 3 November 2020\par \uc2 Blockchain.News\par \uc2 BLCRNW\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2020. Worldmoney Blockchain Management Co., Limited \par \par \uc2 Ripple's chief technical officer (CTO) David Schwartz explained why the company's native XRP cryptocurrency has not been more readily adopted by banks.\par \par \uc2 XRP has long been touted as a bridge currency between fiats, enabling transactions to be conducted without any delays in processing time and free of intermediary fees. Despite its monopoly in the international remittance market, this year has proved to be challenging for Ripple. In explaining why banks have been slow to leverage XRP for cross-border payments, Schwartz {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://twitter.com/JoelKatz/status/1321318681566040066"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 explained}}}\uc2  via \uc2 Twitter\uc2 :\par \par \uc2 I think there are a combination of obstacles. Regulatory uncertainty, last mile problems, fear of reprisals from existing partners, and so on. Another big thing is that the very best customers are ones that are going to use bridge assets to build new products.\par \par \uc2 In addition to this, the Ripple CTO said that the fact that XRP was relatively new as a product could serve to justify why adoption has been lacking.\par \par \uc2 The bridge currency failed to make the list of digital assets that \uc2 PayPal\uc2  has {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://blockchain.news/news/paypal-finally-enables-cryptocurrency-payments-via-its-platform"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 integrated}}}\uc2  for use on its payments platform. Recently, \uc2 PayPal\uc2  introduced cryptocurrency payments as well as digital wallets. Through the new service, \uc2 PayPal\uc2  customers can now purchase items and receive payments for goods and services using Bitcoin (BTC), Ethereum (ETH), \uc2 Litecoin\uc2  (LTC), and Bitcoin Cash (BTC).\par \par \uc2 The news comes at a time when blockchain companies have been aiming to decrease their \uc2 environmental\uc2  impact. With cryptocurrency adoption on the rise, Ripple has tackled the issue of leveraging renewable energy by partnering with EW Zero to deliver sustainable solutions across the blockchain. In addressing this, Schwartz {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://twitter.com/JoelKatz"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 said}}}\uc2 :\par \par \uc2 "Love that crypto is going mainstream, but the enviro impact went way up, esp if you only support energy heavy assets. XRP was built specifically to use negligible amts of energy. In good news, there's a tool to decarbonize emissions for ANY blockchain."\par \par \uc2 The fintech firm has been aiming to deliver carbon neutrality by 2030, through renewable energy solutions and the use of carbon removal technology. This year has been filled with new challenges for Ripple, as the fintech company has also recently been considering a move from the United States, with Ripple CEO Brad Garlinghouse {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://blockchain.news/news/us-blockchain-firm-ripple-considers-relocation-uk-singapore-better-crypto-regulatory-clarity"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 asserting}}}\uc2  that the cryptocurrency regulations in the UK, Singapore, and Japan, may be more beneficial for Ripple operations.\par \par \uc2 Document BLCRNW0020201103egb300002\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw200\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal3000\pichgoal600
