\par\par \uc2 Technology\par \b \uc2 Auto Giants Consortium MOBI Reveals First Blockchain-based EVGI Standard\b0\par\par\uc2 Godfrey Benjamin \par \uc2 371 \uc2 words\par \uc2 12 October 2020\par \uc2 Blockchain.News\par \uc2 BLCRNW\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2020. Worldmoney Blockchain Management Co., Limited \par \par \uc2 The Mobility Open Blockchain Initiative (MOBI) a consortium backed by Honda, \uc2 General Motors Company\uc2  and \uc2 IBM\uc2  amongst others has {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/mobi-announces-the-first-electric-vehicle-grid-integration-standard-on-blockchain-in-collaboration-with-honda-pge-and-gm-among-others-301147088.html"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 launched }}}\uc2  a blockchain-based standard for Electric Vehicle Grid Integration (EVGI).\par \par \uc2 The Need For a Standard In The Electric Vehicle Industry\par \par \uc2 With the rapid transformation of mother earth owing to \uc2 climate change\uc2  implications, several companies following government regulations have resorted to the development of unique frameworks to alter their processes to adhere to \uc2 sustainability\uc2  guidelines. This move prompted players in the automotive industry to develop electric-based vehicles to solve the problem of carbon emissions.\par \par \uc2 With electric vehicles becoming commonplace in the world today, a new challenge revolving around charging stations to help balance the costs of EV batteries. Herein is where the MOBI blockchain initiative comes to play. The blockchain-initiative will serve as the world's first global standard incorporating blockchain technology into a decentralized vehicle charging system.\par \par \uc2 The technical design released by the EVGI working group provides guidelines bothering on three core use cases including Vehicle to Grid Integration (V2G), Tokenized Carbon Credits (TCC), and Peer to Peer (P2P) applications and industry actors though not mandated to follow any specific template in building these decentralized applications to help enhance energy usage and efficiency, they will be obligated to draw from the laid down fundamentals of the three use cases.\par \par \uc2 "Implementing the EVGI Standard will provide a variety of benefits for players on all sides of the electric vehicle and charging ecosystem," said Tram Vo, MOBI's COO and Founder. "Electric vehicles, chargers, and electricity producers can have a secure identity, communicate with a standard messaging format, and automatically record transactions such as charging, generation, and exchange on a distributed ledger."\par \par \uc2 Auto Manufacturers and Blockchain Solutions\par \par \uc2 The auto industry is one of the biggest promoters of blockchain technology particularly for {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://blockchain.news/news/what-are-the-roles-of-microsoft-azure-and-amazon-web-services-in-bmw-groups-blockchain-pilot"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 enhancing supply chain operations}}}\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 Besides \uc2 BMW\uc2 , other car brands have leveraged the power of blockchain technology. For instance, Volvo Cars {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://blockchain.news/news/volvo-cars-invests-london-blockchain-firm-reduce-carbon-dioxide-footprint"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 invested}}}\uc2  in London-based blockchain firm Circulor to develop a blockchain solution to help track and reduce the company's car Carbon Dioxide footprint.\par \par \uc2 General Motors Company\uc2  has also {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://blockchain.news/news/general-motors-files-patent-blockchain-based-autonomous-vehicle-navigation-map"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 integrated}}}\uc2  blockchain technology for autonomous vehicle navigation maps.\par \par \uc2 Document BLCRNW0020201012egac00002\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw200\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal3000\pichgoal600
