\par\par \uc2 Europe\par \b \uc2 European Blockchain Service Infrastructure PCP to Begin\u8212\'20\'14Why it Could Benefit XRP and BTC\b0\par\par\uc2 Lucas Cacioli \par \uc2 501 \uc2 words\par \uc2 1 October 2020\par \uc2 Blockchain.News\par \uc2 BLCRNW\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2020. Worldmoney Blockchain Management Co., Limited \par \par \uc2 The \uc2 European Commission\uc2  is looking for new blockchain solutions for the European Blockchain Service Infrastructure (EBSI). The EBSI aims to deliver EU-wide cross-border public services using blockchain technology with the highest standards of security and privacy. In December {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://ted.europa.eu/TED/notice/udl?uri=TED:NOTICE:590329-2019:TEXT:EN:HTML"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 last year}}}\uc2 , the EC began an open market consultation putting out a call for tenders with the aim of implementing a Pre-Commercial Procurement (PCP) in cooperation with and building on the work of the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://ec.europa.eu/digital-single-market/en/news/european-countries-join-blockchain-partnership"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 European Blockchain Partnership (EBP)}}}\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 The EBP is an effort between the EC, all EU Member States, and some countries of the \uc2 European Economic Area\uc2  to deliver together the European Blockchain Services Infrastructure (EBSI). The PCP is designed to challenge industry from the demand side to develop innovative solutions for public sector needs and it provides a first customer reference that enables companies to create a competitive advantage on the market. The conclusions of the open market consultation should be {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://ec.europa.eu/digital-single-market/en/news/european-blockchain-pre-commercial-procurement"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 published}}}\uc2  early next month, October 2020.\par \par \uc2 The EBSI will be a public infrastructure with high requirements of scalability and throughput, interoperability, security, robustness, reduced \uc2 environmental\uc2  footprint, energy efficiency and continuity of the service and should be deployed within the next 3 years.\par \par \uc2 The EC, EBP, and Rise of Digital Payments Like XRP\par \par \uc2 Based on the conclusions of the open market consultation, the coming PCP is expected to focus on the development of future capacities for EBSI in view of supporting new types of use cases that involve a high volume of transactions concerning physical or digital objects.\par \par \uc2 There are currently large gaps in existing blockchain solutions to enable the delivery of more demanding cross-border blockchain services, one such area is instant payments. Recently the EC {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://blockchain.news/news/european-commission-crypto-regulation-framework-new-digital-finance-package"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 proposed}}}\uc2  a new {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://ec.europa.eu/finance/docs/law/200924-crypto-assets-proposal_en.pdf"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 regulatory framework}}}\uc2  that seeks to offer more clarity about the crypto space in its member states.\par \par \uc2 The proposal stipulates the urge for a sound legal framework for crypto assets as current EU financial services laws have previously left them out.\par \par \uc2 The Commission noted that more stringent requirements might be necessitated for stablecoins as they have the likelihood of being widely adopted. As a result, a bespoke regime for stablecoins and crypto assets should come in handy in areas like wallet services and crypto exchanges.\par \par \uc2 The EC's new legal framework could benefit technology such as that developed by the payment solutions company Ripple. Through its {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://blockchain.news/news/ripple-1-billion-xrp-price-trades-heavy-us-dollar-loses-value-inflation"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 On-Demand Liquidity}}}\uc2  payment solution, Ripple is able to offer low-cost instant cross-border payment services with XRP.\par \par \uc2 A European regulated framework could also create more legitimacy for cryptocurrency payments with the main tokens like Bitcoin and Ethereum and \uc2 Litecoin\uc2 . However, it will depend on the legal framework presented by the \uc2 European Commission\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 According to a {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://uk.reuters.com/article/eu-cryptoassets/eu-to-introduce-crypto-assets-regime-by-2024-eu-documents-say-idUSL8N2GE4V6"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 report }}}\uc2 by Reuters:\par \par \uc2 By 2024, the EU should put in place a comprehensive framework enabling the uptake of distributed ledger technology (DLT) and crypto-assets in the financial sector [ ] It should also address the risks associated with these technologies.\par \par \uc2 Document BLCRNW0020201001ega10000a\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw200\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal3000\pichgoal600
