\par\par \uc2 Technology\par \b \uc2 Dubai Economy Gets Powered by UAE KYC Blockchain Platform for Safe Digital Customer Onboarding\b0\par\par\uc2 Brian Njuguna \par \uc2 447 \uc2 words\par \uc2 30 July 2020\par \uc2 Blockchain.News\par \uc2 BLCRNW\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2020. Worldmoney Blockchain Management Co., Limited \par \par \uc2 The Dubai economy has gone live on the UAE KYC (Know-Your-Customer) blockchain platform making instant bank accounting functionality, secure digital customer onboarding, and sharing of verified data between financial institutions and licensing authorities possible.\par \par \uc2 As reported by local outlet Khaleej Times on July 28, this {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.khaleejtimes.com/business/local/dubai-economy-emirates-nbd-go-live-with-uae-kyc-blockchain-platform"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2  initiative }}}\uc2  is powered by norbloc, a leading blockchain KYC technology firm.\par \par \uc2 Blockchain-based ecosystem\par \par \uc2 Emirates NBD\uc2 , a leading bank in the UAE, is the first banking group to be part of the project based on its active and operational bank accounts. Other banks like \uc2 Commercial Bank of Dubai\uc2 , RAKBANK, \uc2 HSBC\uc2 , and ADCB are expected to follow suit.\par \par \uc2 This blockchain-enabled ecosystem is set to be adopted nationwide in the exchange of authentic KYC data as it is already supported by the \uc2 Central Bank of UAE\uc2  and Smart Dubai.\par \par \uc2 The CEO of Business Registration Licensing (BRL) field in Dubai Economy, Omar Bushahab, noted, We are very proud to announce that the UAE KYC Blockchain Platform is now production-ready with over 120 companies already instantly onboarded by \uc2 Emirates NBD\uc2  with active and operational bank accounts.\par \par \uc2 He added, This marks a key milestone in establishing a UAE-wide ecosystem for KYC data sharing and instant digital onboarding of companies by financial institutions. It is in alignment with the government's vision around digitization and paperless as crucial strategies that enable continuation and \uc2 sustainability\uc2 , especially during these challenging times, further enhancing the ease of doing business in the country.\par \par \uc2 The Dubai economy has already shifted its active trade licenses to the blockchain platform. This represents more than 40% of their overall number in the UAE.\par \par \uc2 Seamless data retrieval\par \par \uc2 By leveraging on the blockchain platform, participating financial institutions are seamlessly retrieving customer data and getting real-time updates on the same.\par \par \uc2 The blockchain-based banking solution aim to boost customers' satisfactory rates by giving them more time to focus on their businesses.\par \par \uc2 Astyanax Kanakakis, norbloc CEO, asserted, The commitment of Dubai Economy, leading financial institutions such as \uc2 Emirates NBD\uc2 , Dubai Government, and the UAE Government to this initiative demonstrates a proactive and ambitious mindset, and positions the UAE as one of the first countries taking significant measures towards creating a digital low touch economy with simplified processes ensuring that business can continue to thrive in the post-COVID environment.\par \par \uc2 This project seeks to place the UAE as one of the first nations to deploy a countrywide blockchain data-sharing ecosystem. Blockchain-based solutions are continually being embraced globally as leading big four firm Deloitte recently {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://blockchain.news/news/deloitte-partners-chronicled-fight-counterfeit-medication-blockchain-technology"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2  partnered }}}\uc2  with Chronicled to tame counterfeit medication through this cutting-edge technology.\par \par \uc2 Document BLCRNW0020200730eg7u00004\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw300\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4500\pichgoal600
