\par\par \b \uc2 BNC Research: DAOs are disrupting the governance & wealth distribution model of the corporation\b0\par\par\uc2 576 \uc2 words\par \uc2 25 June 2019\par \uc2 Brave New Coin\par \uc2 BRACOI\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 \u169\'00\'A9 2019. Brave New Coin Limited \par \par \uc2 This report looks at the future constraints for the shareholder model in its current form, and why decentralized autonomous organizations (DAOs) will be superior to today\u8217\'20\'19s corporate firm structure. For investors, DAOs will eventually become a less risky investment class compared to shares in a regular company, offering more predictable ROI and better passive returns than most stock dividends - while also minimizing two of the greatest risks in corporate operations - human error and executive self-interest.\par \par \uc2 Decentralized autonomous organizations (DAOs) are shaping the future of work and corporate governance in the Information Age. With meritocratic governance that better aligns stakeholders' interests, DAOs have the potential to reduce the social, economic and ecological fragility in our systems perpetuated by the shareholder model.\par \par \uc2 A DAO can be summarized as an organization of people who communicate with each other via a "network protocol," communicating with one another through an online ruleset but reaching governance consensus with offline diplomacy. DAOs are the end-point of the 'gig economy' which to date has been championed by platforms like Uber and \uc2 Airbnb\uc2 , but will be truly global cooperatives and their value distributed to stakeholders - not just shareholders and executives.\par \par {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://bravenewcoin.com/insights/libra-how-facebook-and-others-plan-to-meet-the-daily-financial-needs-of"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Facebook has also just announced}}}\uc2  it intends to turn its crypto project 'Libra', into a decentralized autonomous organization utilizing a native governance token (the Libra Investment Token), which is a huge aboutface for a company notorious for its centralized control.\par \par {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://images.ctfassets.net/sdlntm3tthp6/3JbBywuxTJ49TyM1cabRgK/48cea91201a8e11c4fa3f0657b4effd3/Degree_of_DAO.JPG"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Click to view image.}}}\par \par \uc2 As nature of 'the firm' is rapidly changing in the Information Age intangible assets are now regarded as the most important driver of corporate value as opposed to tangibles accumulated in the industrial model. This poses problems for those still operating in the \u8216\'20\'18old model\u8217\'20\'19 including:\par \par \uc2 * Difficulty in valuing intangible assets in digitally native organizations\par \par \uc2 * A continuing decline in corporate accounting and auditing standards\par \par \uc2 * New forms of fundraising, such as Security Token Offerings - less costly than IPOs\par \par \uc2 * Security tokens offerings which can blend equity rights and debt with governance\par \par \uc2 * Growing social responsibility for corporations to account for \u8216\'20\'18external costs\u8217\'20\'19\par \par \uc2 * Mounting social costs for corporations such as \uc2 climate change\uc2  value-at-risk.\par \par \uc2 * The concentration of share value and corporate earnings in growth and tech stocks invested through passive strategies increasing systemic risk in the stockmarket\par \par \uc2 In this {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://mailchi.mp/bravenewcoin.com/the-future-of-the-firm"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 report}}}\uc2  we look at the future constraints for the shareholder model in its current form, the game theory behind mass scale decentralized cooperation and why organizations operating this way will be superior to today\u8217\'20\'19s corporate firm structure.\par \par \uc2 For investors, we see DAOs eventually becoming a less risky investment class compared to shares in a regular company, with more predictable ROI as they minimize two of the greatest risks in the running of a company - human error and self-interests. They also offer better passive returns than most stock dividends in the form of coin-staking and running of masternodes.\par \par {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://images.ctfassets.net/sdlntm3tthp6/1gxNtfAeYNamSZiYsohwSk/a9a8e7d649470958c1f017bdfdc0ed2c/The-future-of-the-firm-thumb.jpg"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Click to view image.}}}\par \par {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://mailchi.mp/bravenewcoin.com/the-future-of-the-firm"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 DOWNLOAD FREE REPORT}}}\par \par \uc2 THE FUTURE OF THE FIRM: How decentralized autonomous organizations are disrupting the centuries old governance and wealth distribution model of the corporation.\par \par \uc2 In a tectonic shift for corporate governance, \uc2 Facebook\uc2  has announced it intends to turn its crypto project Libra into a decentralized autonomous organization (DAO). Read this report to understand what a DAO is, how will they disrupt legacy financial and corporate systems - and where investor value will lie in the new economy of distributed organizations.\par \par \uc2 // {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://mailchi.mp/bravenewcoin.com/the-future-of-the-firm"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Access the full report here}}}\par \par \uc2 Document BRACOI0020190731ef6p000a8\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw300\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4500\pichgoal600
