ent Token), which is a huge aboutface for a company notorious for its centralized control.\par \par {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://images.ctfassets.net/sdlntm3tthp6/2EmPrImBf2aA5c6IXx6BSs/411f5ee9a4def28aef6ee748459c717c/Degrees-of-Decentralized-Organizations.png"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Click to view image.}}}\par \par \uc2 As nature of 'the firm' is rapidly changing in the Information Age intangible assets are now regarded as the most important driver of corporate value as opposed to tangibles accumulated in the industrial model. This poses problems for those still operating in the \u8216\'20\'18old model\u8217\'20\'19 including:\par \par \uc2 * Difficulty in valuing intangible assets in digitally native organizations\par \par \uc2 * A continuing decline in corporate accounting and auditing standards\par \par \uc2 * New forms of fundraising, such as Security Token Offerings - less costly than IPOs\par \par \uc2 * Security tokens offerings which can blend equity rights and debt with governance\par \par \uc2 * Growing social responsibility for corporations to account for \u8216\'20\'18external costs\u8217\'20\'19\par \par \uc2 * Mounting social costs for corporations such as \uc2 climate change\uc2  value-at-risk.\par \par \uc2 * The concentration of share value and corporate earnings in growth and tech stocks invested through passive strategies increasing systemic risk in the stockmarket\par \par \uc2 In this {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://mailchi.mp/bravenewcoin.com/the-future-of-the-firm"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 report}}}\uc2  we look at the future constraints for the shareholder model in its current form, the game theory behind mass scale decentralized cooperation and why organizations operating this way will be superior to today\u8217\'20\'19s corporate firm structure.\par \par \uc2 For investors, we see DAOs eventually becoming a less risky investment class compared to shares in a regular company, with more predictable ROI as they minimize two of the greatest risks in the running of a company - human error and self-interests. They also offer better passive returns than most stock dividends in the form of coin-staking and running of masternodes.\par \par {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://images.ctfassets.net/sdlntm3tthp6/7u0jzkxUOU958VdPIK3wwR/3f76eb34786b4b36ffccca93610faded/The-future-of-the-firm-thumb.jpg"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Click to view image.}}}\par \par {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://mailchi.mp/bravenewcoin.com/the-future-of-the-firm"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 DOWNLOAD FREE REPORT}}}\par \par \uc2 THE FUTURE OF THE FIRM: How decentralized autonomous organizations are disrupting the centuries old governance and wealth distribution model of the corporation.\par \par \uc2 In a tectonic shift for corporate governance, \uc2 Facebook\uc2  has announced it intends to turn its crypto project Libra into a decentralized autonomous organization (DAO). Read this report to understand what a DAO is, how will they disrupt legacy financial and corporate systems - and where investor value will lie in the new economy of distributed organizations.\par \par \uc2 // {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://mailchi.mp/bravenewcoin.com/the-future-of-the-firm"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Access the full report here}}}\par \par \uc2 Document BRACOI0020190731ef6p00021\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw300\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4500\pichgoal600
